&q;,&q;process.param.description-v.import&q;:&q;test run - do not actually import items&q;,&q;process.param.description-x.import&q;:&q;do not load or expect content bitstreams&q;,&q;process.param.description-p.import&q;:&q;apply template&q;,&q;process.param.description-R.import&q;:&q;resume a failed import (add only)&q;,&q;process.param.description-q.import&q;:&q;don&s;t display metadata&q;,&q;process.param.description-h.import&q;:&q;help&q;,&q;process.param.description-f.import-openaire-events&q;:&q;Import data from Openaire quality assurance broker JSON file. This parameter is mutually exclusive to the email parameter.&q;,&q;process.param.description-e.import-openaire-events&q;:&q;Email related to the subscriptions to import data from Openaire broker. This parameter is mutually exclusive to the file parameter.&q;,&q;process.param.description-s.import-openaire-suggestions&q;:&q;Single researcher UUID&q;,&q;process.param.description-s.import-publications&q;:&q;the name of the external service to be queried (\&q;scopus\&q; or \&q;wos\&q;)&q;,&q;process.param.description-e.import-publications&q;:&q;email of the eperson performing the import&q;,&q;process.param.description-l.import-publications&q;:&q;the max number of search to be performed. If no limit is provided, the default one will be used&q;,&q;process.param.description-r.index-discovery&q;:&q;remove an Item, Collection or Community from index based on its handle&q;,&q;process.param.description-i.index-discovery&q;:&q;add or update an Item, Collection or Community based on its handle or uuid&q;,&q;process.param.description-t.index-discovery&q;:&q;limit the update operation to a specific indexable object type (such as Item, ClaimedTask, PoolTask, etc.), can be combined with -f and -s.&q;,&q;process.param.description-c.index-discovery&q;:&q;clean existing index removing any documents that no longer exist in the db&q;,&q;process.param.description-d.index-discovery&q;:&q;delete all records from existing index&q;,&q;p